  "response": "# Custom Disclosure Widget Accessibility Design Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** Use a11y-planner protocol. Review with a11y-critic after implementation.  \n> **Compliance target:** WCAG 2.2 AA  \n> **Users who need accessibility:** Screen reader users, keyboard-only users, low vision users, touch users  \n> **Assistive technologies:** NVDA on Windows, VoiceOver on macOS, keyboard-only navigation  \n\n**Feature:** A reusable React disclosure/accordion component with multiple independently expandable FAQ-style sections.  \n**Risk Level:** Low  \n**Component/Page Type:** Disclosure / Accordion-style content reveal  \n\n---\n\n## Scope & Context\n\nThis component lets users expand and collapse multiple content sections. Each section has a trigger button and an associated content panel. Multiple panels may be open at the same time, so this is **not** an exclusive accordion/tab pattern.\n\nThe correct pattern is the **WAI-ARIA APG Disclosure Pattern**:  \nhttps://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/disclosure/\n\nThis plan does **not** claim the component is a tablist, menu, tree, or single-select accordion. It should not use `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selected`, or roving tabindex.\n\n---\n\n## Semantic Structure Plan\n\nUse native semantic elements wherever possible.\n\n### Structure Stub\n\n```html\n<section aria-labelledby=\"faq-heading\">\n  <h2 id=\"faq-heading\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n  <div class=\"disclosure-item\">\n    <h3>\n      <button\n        type=\"button\"\n        aria-expanded=\"false\"\n        aria-controls=\"panel-shipping\"\n        id=\"trigger-shipping\"\n      >\n        Shipping information\n        <span aria-hidden=\"true\">+</span>\n      </button>\n    </h3>\n\n    <div\n      id=\"panel-shipping\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"trigger-shipping\"\n      hidden\n    >\n      <p>Shipping content goes here.</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n```\n\n### Semantic Requirements\n\n- Use a real `<button>` for each trigger.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 2.1.1 Keyboard and 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- Place each button inside a heading when the disclosure title is part of the page outline.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 1.3.1 Info and Relationships and 2.4.6 Headings and Labels.\n- Use native `hidden` or conditional rendering for collapsed panels.\n  - Prevents hidden content from remaining in the reading order or tab order.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 1.3.2 Meaningful Sequence and 2.4.3 Focus Order.\n- Do not use `aria-hidden` alone to hide collapsed panels if they contain focusable content.\n  - `aria-hidden` does not remove elements from keyboard focus.\n\n---\n\n## Interaction Pattern Design\n\n### Interactive Elements Table\n\n| Widget | APG Pattern | Keyboard Model | ARIA Attributes | WCAG Citation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Disclosure trigger button | [APG Disclosure Pattern](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/disclosure/) | `Tab` moves to button. `Enter` toggles. `Space` toggles. | `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls` | WCAG 2.1.1, 2.4.3, 4.1.2 |\n| Disclosure panel | APG Disclosure controlled content | Panel is reached by normal tab order only when visible and contains focusable content. | `id`, optional `aria-labelledby` | WCAG 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 4.1.2 |\n\n### Keyboard Interaction Model\n\n- `Tab`: moves focus through each disclosure button in DOM order.\n- `Shift + Tab`: moves focus backward through each disclosure button in DOM order.\n- `Enter`: toggles the focused disclosure button.\n- `Space`: toggles the focused disclosure button.\n- Arrow keys: not required. This is not a composite widget.\n- `Escape`: not required. This is not a modal, menu, or popover.\n\nThe button remains focused after toggling. Focus should not automatically move into the panel because APG Disclosure does not require that, and unexpected focus movement can disorient keyboard and screen reader users.\n\n---\n\n## ARIA Implementation\n\n### Required Attributes\n\n- `aria-expanded=\"false\"` on each trigger when its panel is collapsed.\n  - Changes to `aria-expanded=\"true\"` when expanded.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- `aria-controls=\"[panel-id]\"` on each trigger.\n  - References the `id` of the controlled panel.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- Unique `id` on every panel.\n  - Required so `aria-controls` points to exactly one panel.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- Optional `aria-labelledby=\"[button-id]\"` on each panel.\n  - Helps associate panel content with its trigger.\n  - Satisfies WCAG 1.3.1 Info and Relationships.\n\n### Do Not Use\n\n- Do not use `role=\"button\"` on a `<div>` or `<span>` when a native `<button>` can be used.\n- Do not use `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, or `aria-selected`.\n- Do not use `title` as the accessible name.\n- Do not expose decorative `+`, `-`, `\u25b2`, or `\u25bc` symbols to screen readers. Wrap them in `aria-hidden=\"true\"`.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Management Plan\n\nNo focus trap is needed.\n\nExpected focus behavior:\n\n1. User tabs to the first disclosure button.\n2. User presses `Enter` or `Space`.\n3. The panel expands or collapses.\n4. Focus remains on the trigger button.\n5. User continues tabbing to the next disclosure button or into visible panel content if the panel contains focusable elements.\n\nIf a panel is collapsed, any focusable elements inside it must be removed from the tab order by using `hidden`, `display: none`, conditional rendering, or equivalent.\n\nFocus indicators must be visible on every button:\n\n- Minimum 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors.\n- Prefer a two-color focus indicator, such as outline plus box-shadow.\n- Use `:focus-visible` for custom styling.\n- Satisfies WCAG 2.4.7 Focus Visible, 2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured, and 2.4.13 Focus Appearance.\n\nTouch targets should be at least 24x24 CSS px, with 44x44 CSS px preferred for mobile.\n\n---\n\n## State Communication Design\n\n| State | Visual Indicator | Programmatic Indicator | ARIA Attribute | WCAG Citation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Collapsed | Closed icon, panel hidden | Button exposes collapsed state | `aria-expanded=\"false\"` | WCAG 4.1.2 |\n| Expanded | Open icon, panel visible | Button exposes expanded state | `aria-expanded=\"true\"` | WCAG 4.1.2 |\n| Disabled, if supported | Muted styling plus text/icon cue | Native disabled state | `disabled` on `<button>` | WCAG 4.1.2 |\n| Focused | Visible outline/ring | Browser or custom focus state | Native focus | WCAG 2.4.7, 2.4.13 |\n\nScreen reader expectation:\n\n- Collapsed trigger: \u201cShipping information, button, collapsed.\u201d\n- Expanded trigger: \u201cShipping information, button, expanded.\u201d\n\nNo live region is needed because the user directly caused the state change and `aria-expanded` communicates the new state.\n\n---\n\n## Visual Accessibility Plan\n\n- Text contrast must be at least 4.5:1.\n  - WCAG 1.4.3 Contrast Minimum.\n- Button borders, icons, and focus indicators must be at least 3:1.\n  - WCAG 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast.\n- Do not rely on color alone to show expanded/collapsed state.\n  - Use text, icon shape, position, or rotation in addition to color.\n  - WCAG 1.4.1 Use of Color.\n- Decorative state icons must be hidden from assistive tech if `aria-expanded` already communicates the state.\n  - WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- Use relative sizing and allow 200% zoom without horizontal scrolling.\n  - WCAG 1.4.4 Resize Text and 1.4.10 Reflow.\n- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` if panel open/close is animated.\n  - WCAG 2.3.3 Animation from Interactions.\n\n---\n\n## Content Accessibility Plan\n\n- Button text must describe the content being revealed.\n  - Good: \u201cShipping information\u201d\n  - Poor: \u201cRead more\u201d\n  - WCAG 2.4.6 Headings and Labels.\n- If disclosure content contains links, link text must be descriptive.\n  - WCAG 2.4.4 Link Purpose.\n- DOM order must match visual order.\n  - WCAG 1.3.2 Meaningful Sequence.\n- If disclosure content includes images, provide appropriate `alt` text or `alt=\"\"` for decorative images.\n  - WCAG 1.1.1 Non-text Content.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Cases\n\n- Keyboard: `Tab` focuses each disclosure button in order.\n- Keyboard: `Enter` toggles the focused disclosure.\n- Keyboard: `Space` toggles the focused disclosure.\n- Focus: focus remains on the trigger after toggle.\n- State: `aria-expanded` changes from `false` to `true` when opened.\n- State: `aria-expanded` changes from `true` to `false` when closed.\n- Relationship: `aria-controls` references the correct visible/hidden panel `id`.\n- Hidden content: collapsed panels are not reachable by keyboard.\n- Screen reader: NVDA and VoiceOver announce button name, role, and expanded/collapsed state.\n- Visual: focus indicator is visible and meets contrast requirements.\n- Mobile: trigger target size is at least 24x24 CSS px, preferably 44x44.\n- Reduced motion: panel animation is removed or minimized when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` is active.\n- DOM verification: confirm ARIA attributes are on the actual `<button>`, not on a wrapper.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Disclosure Component\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Reusable disclosure component file\n- Component tests\n- Storybook/design-system example, if applicable\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<section aria-labelledby=\"disclosure-group-heading\">\n  <h2 id=\"disclosure-group-heading\">Section heading</h2>\n\n  <div>\n    <h3>\n      <button\n        type=\"button\"\n        id=\"trigger-id\"\n        aria-expanded=\"false\"\n        aria-controls=\"panel-id\"\n      >\n        Trigger label\n        <span aria-hidden=\"true\">+</span>\n      </button>\n    </h3>\n\n    <div\n      id=\"panel-id\"\n      aria-labelledby=\"trigger-id\"\n      hidden\n    >\n      Panel content\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n```\n\n**ARIA Attributes:**\n\n- `aria-expanded`: communicates expanded/collapsed state. WCAG 4.1.2.\n- `aria-controls`: associates trigger with controlled panel. WCAG 4.1.2.\n- `aria-labelledby` on panel, optional but recommended. WCAG 1.3.1.\n- `aria-hidden=\"true\"` only on decorative icons. WCAG 1.1.1 and 4.1.2.\n\n**Keyboard Interactions:**\n\n- `Tab`: focus next trigger or visible focusable content.\n- `Shift + Tab`: focus previous trigger or visible focusable content.\n- `Enter`: toggle current panel.\n- `Space`: toggle current panel.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Verify native button receives focus.\n- Verify `Enter` toggles panel.\n- Verify `Space` toggles panel.\n- Verify multiple panels can be open simultaneously.\n- Verify collapsed panel is hidden from keyboard navigation.\n- Verify screen reader announces expanded/collapsed state through `aria-expanded`.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- WCAG 1.3.1 Info and Relationships.\n- WCAG 1.3.2 Meaningful Sequence.\n- WCAG 1.4.1 Use of Color.\n- WCAG 1.4.3 Contrast Minimum.\n- WCAG 1.4.11 Non-text Contrast.\n- WCAG 2.1.1 Keyboard.\n- WCAG 2.4.3 Focus Order.\n- WCAG 2.4.7 Focus Visible.\n- WCAG 2.4.13 Focus Appearance.\n- WCAG 2.5.8 Target Size.\n- WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n\n---\n\n## a11y-Critic Review Checkpoints\n\n| Checkpoint | After Task | Focus Areas |\n|---|---|---|\n| \ud83d\udd0d 1 | Disclosure component implementation | Verify APG Disclosure pattern, native buttons, `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, hidden panel behavior, keyboard toggle behavior, visible focus indicator, and screen reader announcements |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- WAI-ARIA APG Disclosure Pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/disclosure/\n- WCAG 2.2 Quick Reference: https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/quickref/\n- WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices Guide: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/",
